title: VA - Grammy's Greatest Moments Volume II - 1994
description:
Grammy&#039;s Greatest Moments, Vol. 2 - 1994

1. We Didn&#039;t Start The Fire - Billy Joel
2. Heart Of Rock &#039;n Roll - Huey Lewis And The News
3. Come Together - Aerosmith
4. Vision Of Love - Mariah Carey
5. Whart A Fool Believes - Doobie Brothers
6. Save The Best For Last - Vanessa Williams
7. Respect - Aretha Frankllin
8. How Am I Supposed To Live Without You - Michael Bolton
9. If You Let Me Stay - Terence Trent D&#039;Arby
10. Constant Craving - K.D. Lang
11. One Monent In Time - Whitney Houston
12. Tears In Heaven - Eric Clapton 

Grammy&#039;s Greatest Moments, Vol. 2 gathers more live performances from the awards-show telecast; while there isn&#039;t much rhyme or reason as to which songs were selected here, or what years they were taken from, the common thread of high performance quality helps tie the collection together. The concentration tends to be on the &#039;80s and &#039;90s, and on mainstream pop/rock, although there&#039;s a bit of R&B (Terence Trent D&#039;Arby&#039;s "If You Let Me Stay," Aretha Franklin&#039;s "Respect") and hard rock (Aerosmith&#039;s "Come Together"). Other highlights include Mariah Carey&#039;s "Vision of Love," Billy Joel&#039;s "We Didn&#039;t Start the Fire," k.d. lang&#039;s "Constant Craving," Eric Clapton&#039;s "Tears in Heaven," and Huey Lewis and the News&#039; "The Heart of Rock &#039;n&#039; Roll." ~ Steve Huey, All Music Guide
